	<Title>
		Buying prescription drugs online?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Ordering prescription drugs online can save you time and sometimes even money, but you must be careful. When you&apos;re ordering drugs online, remember simple do&apos;s and don&apos;ts. 1. Consult your doctor first. 2. Use a licensed pharmacy that offers access to a registered pharmacist. 3. Read the pharmacy&apos;s privacy and security policies. 4. Don&apos;t use a site that bypasses prescriptions. 5. Steer clear of sites that don&apos;t provide a street address and phone number. 6. When you get the medication, make sure it matches your prescription.&lt;/p&gt;
